hands_on_practices.solution:
1. From the definition $\theta(z)=r_s/[(1+z)d_A(z)]$.
→ for two models at same $z$, the ratio is
$$R=\frac{\theta_{\rm open}}{\theta_{\rm flat}}
=\frac{r_s/[(1+z)d_A^{\rm open}(z)]}{r_s/[(1+z)d_A^{\rm flat}(z)]}
=\frac{d_A^{\rm flat}(z)}{d_A^{\rm open}(z)}\,. $$
2. The Mattig formula for a matter-only universe is
$$d_A(z)
=\frac{2c}{H_0(1+z)^2\Omega_{m,0}^2}\Bigl[\Omega_{m,0}z+(\Omega_{m,0}-2)\bigl(\sqrt{1+\Omega_{m,0}z}-1\bigr)\Bigr]\,. $$
3. For the flat Einstein–de Sitter case, set $\Omega_{m,0}=1$:
$$d_A^{\rm flat}(z)
=\frac{2c}{H_0(1+z)^2}\bigl[z+(-1)(\sqrt{1+z}-1)\bigr]
=\frac{2c}{H_0}\frac{\sqrt{1+z}-1}{(1+z)^{3/2}}\,. $$
4. Form the ratio:
$$R
=\frac{d_A^{\rm flat}(z)}{d_A^{\rm open}(z)}
=\frac{\frac{2c}{H_0}\,\frac{\sqrt{1+z}-1}{(1+z)^{3/2}}}
{\frac{2c}{H_0(1+z)^2\Omega_{m,0}^2}\bigl[\Omega_{m,0}z+(\Omega_{m,0}-2)(\sqrt{1+\Omega_{m,0}z}-1)\bigr]}
=\frac{\Omega_{m,0}^2(1+z)^{1/2}(\sqrt{1+z}-1)}
{\Omega_{m,0}z+(\Omega_{m,0}-2)(\sqrt{1+\Omega_{m,0}z}-1)}\,. $$
